Argentine Stocks: Banco Macro, Banco Santander, Petrobras Rise

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-09-26T20:20:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-26/argentine-stocks-banco-macro-and-banco-santander-advance.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 4 p.m.  New York  time.  The Merval Index rose 0.9 percent to 2,504.95.  Banco Macro SA (BMA)   rose 2.5 percent to 10.1 pesos, its
second day of gains. Argentina’s largest lender by market share
purchased 378,795 of its own shares, according to a statement
posted Sept. 23 on the website of the Buenos Aires exchange. The
bank announced Sept. 15 plans to buy as much as 200 million
pesos in shares.  Banco Santander SA (SAN)   gained 7.1 percent, the most in
almost four months, to 37.5 pesos. The Spanish lender rose after
finance ministers and central bankers urged policy makers in
Europe to intensify efforts to contain the region’s debt crisis
following meetings with the  International Monetary Fund .  Petroleo Brasileiro SA (PETR4)  , Brazil’s state-controlled
oil company, rose 4.1 percent to 54.80 pesos as crude prices
climbed in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
